  responsibilities_md = E'- Design, document, and implement technical solutions for systems of various types and sizes, ensuring integration, maintenance, and migration considerations\n- Provide comprehensive software architecture design and lead technical decision-making processes\n- Manage code quality through rigorous code reviews, enforce coding standards, and ensure best practices\n- Define technical guidelines, review alternative approaches, and conduct thorough technical evaluations\n- Collaborate closely with product managers and lead engineers to recommend optimal solutions based on project roadmap\n- Work hands-on as a technical leader/expert architect in projects on a daily basis\n- Continuously stay informed on emerging technologies, frameworks, and tools\n- Develop new project ideas and proof-of-concepts when required by the project roadmap\n- Contribute to presales activities, including preparing technical proposals, effort estimations, and presenting solutions to clients\n- Support recruitment efforts within the company by conducting technical interviews and mentoring team members\n- Participate in architectural review boards and contribute to technology strategy discussions',
  requirements_md = E'- 7+ years of professional software development experience with C#, .NET, ASP.NET Core, Web API, Entity Framework, and SQL Server\n- Solid experience as Software Architect with deep understanding of design patterns, SOLID principles, and clean code practices\n- Strong expertise in database design, SQL optimization, and performance tuning\n- Hands-on experience with Azure or AWS cloud platforms, including services like App Services, Functions, Storage, and databases\n- Deep understanding of Microservices architecture, API Gateway patterns, and distributed systems\n- Experience with DevOps practices, CI/CD pipelines, and Infrastructure as Code (Terraform/ARM templates)\n- Strong focus on Performance optimization, Security best practices, and scalability considerations\n- Familiarity with frontend frameworks such as React, Angular, or Vue.js\n- Experience working and coordinating with global, distributed teams across different time zones\n- Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English\n- Comprehensive knowledge and expertise in Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodologies\n- Experience with Agile/Scrum methodologies and tools like Jira, Confluence\n- Having experience with AI-powered development tools such as GitHub Copilot or similar is a strong plus\n- Bachelor''s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or related field (Master''s preferred)'
WHERE slug = 'nodejs-developer-senior' AND locale = 'en';

