  summary = 'Join our AI team as a Master AI Engineer to build cutting-edge artificial intelligence solutions that push the boundaries of what''s possible. You will lead AI initiatives, research new methodologies, and deploy production-grade ML systems at scale.',
  responsibilities_md = E'- Design, develop, and deploy state-of-the-art AI and machine learning systems for real-world business applications\n- Lead AI research and development initiatives, exploring new algorithms, models, and techniques\n- Architect and implement end-to-end ML pipelines from data ingestion to model deployment and monitoring\n- Mentor and guide AI/ML engineers and data scientists, fostering a culture of innovation and technical excellence\n- Stay at the forefront of AI research, continuously evaluating and adopting latest advancements in deep learning, NLP, computer vision, and reinforcement learning\n- Collaborate with product teams to identify opportunities where AI can create significant business value\n- Design and implement scalable ML infrastructure and MLOps workflows for model training, versioning, and deployment\n- Conduct technical reviews and ensure AI solutions meet high standards of performance, reliability, and ethical considerations\n- Optimize model performance for production environments, balancing accuracy, latency, and computational costs\n- Develop frameworks and tools to accelerate AI development across the organization\n- Lead technical discussions with stakeholders, translating complex AI concepts into business value propositions\n- Contribute to open-source AI projects and publish research findings in relevant conferences or journals\n- Establish best practices for responsible AI development, including fairness, transparency, and bias mitigation\n- Design and implement A/B testing frameworks to measure AI model impact on business metrics',
  requirements_md = E'- Master''s degree or PhD in Computer Science, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, or related quantitative field\n- 8+ years of hands-on experience in AI/ML engineering with proven track record of deploying production ML systems\n- Deep expertise in deep learning frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch, JAX) and neural network architectures\n- Strong foundation in machine learning theory, algorithms, and statistical methods\n- Extensive experience with NLP (transformers, BERT, GPT, etc.) and/or computer vision (CNNs, object detection, segmentation)\n- Proficiency in Python and ML libraries (NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-learn, Hugging Face)\n- Experience with distributed training, model optimization, and serving at scale\n- Strong knowledge of MLOps tools and practices (MLflow, Kubeflow, Weights & Biases, etc.)\n- Hands-on experience with cloud ML platforms (AWS SageMaker, Azure ML, Google Vertex AI)\n- Experience with vector databases and embeddings for RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) applications\n- Strong understanding of model monitoring, A/B testing, and continuous model improvement\n- Experience with containerization (Docker) and orchestration (Kubernetes) for ML workloads\n- Proven ability to work with large-scale datasets and big data technologies (Spark, Hadoop)\n- Strong programming skills with focus on writing production-quality, maintainable code\n- Experience leading technical teams and mentoring junior engineers\n- Excellent communication skills with ability to explain complex AI concepts to diverse audiences\n- Publications in top-tier AI/ML conferences (NeurIPS, ICML, CVPR) or significant contributions to open-source AI projects are highly valued\n- Track record of innovation and staying current with rapidly evolving AI landscape'
WHERE slug = 'ai-engineer-master' AND locale = 'en';

